        "text": "Greetings FoC,\n\nDo you think the butlerian jihad has started or is getting some traction?\n\n<https:\/\/news.ycombinator.com\/item?id=47173121>\n\n<https:\/\/www.anthropic.com\/news\/statement-department-of-war>\n\n<https:\/\/news.ycombinator.com\/item?id=47179553>\n\n<https:\/\/docs.postmarketos.org\/policies-and-processes\/development\/ai-policy.html>\n\nI mean this in the sense of a more mature relationship with Technology? I recently listened to this:\n\n<https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=Kyak9MuzSsc>\n\nThe interview is very interesting, even if the host is a bit strange and self centered. They reach the point where they talk about LLM's and the host is like \"its just too good\" But then andrew mcluhan says this is my LLM ( points to his own brain) and this is my claude( points to his pencil)  Andrew is like a soft and calm voice trying to advocate for better relationship with technology. Check out his twitter for some funny slogans.  They briefly touch on privacy - its just too good. They also talk a few bits about <https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/I._A._Richards#Feedforward> Its very interesting to see them , or at least Andrew talk about Meta Technology Reflection.  I felt  reminded of the snipped before the dune movie where they actually show the story of the butlerian jihad\n\n<https:\/\/www.youtube.com\/watch?v=adV3BbO1Si4&amp;pp=ygUZZHVuZSBtb3ZpZSAxOTg0IHByZSBzdG9yedIHCQm-CgGHKiGM7w%3D%3D>\n\nWhat do you think?",
